      • getValue

        protected java.lang.String getValue(java.util.Map<java.lang.String,java.lang.String> nameToSimpleName,
                                    java.lang.Class type,
                                    boolean cast)
        Return the default value of the type provided.
        Parameters:
        nameToSimpleName - a map of fully qualified java names to simple names, such as "java.lang.Thread" to "Thread". This method takes this map into account to simplify names. This is not just a nicety to make code more readable: in rare cases this is a requirement to avoid compiler errors.
        type - the Class to represent
        cast - true if this should preface the value with a cast (if appropriate). For example: when writing a constructor we shouldn't say "super(null)", because the compiler may flag that as ambiguous. Instead we should say "super( (java.lang.Thread) null)".
        Returns:
        a java representation of a default value for the type provided, such as "0L" (for longs), "'?'" (for chars), "(short)0" (for shorts), or "null" for objects. This method will not return null. (But it may return "null").
